# Death's Activity Economy — Server Setup Guide

This guide explains how to set up server custom content for Death's Activity Economy aliases.

The system can use:

* Death's default GVAR content
* server custom SVAR content
* both together
* locked or unlocked progression
* layered server content packs

The visible command layout is not changed by these settings.

## Main Server Settings

### `activitySources`

Create this server svar:

```text
!svar activitySources {"useGvar":true,"useSvar":true,"priority":"svar","unlockMode":"unlocked","unlockCvar":"activity_unlocks","setupGuideUrl":"https://github.com/Death8673/Activities/blob/main/Setup"}
```

### Options

`useGvar:true` means the aliases can use Death's default GVAR content.

`useGvar:false` means the aliases ignore Death's default GVAR content.

`useSvar:true` means the aliases can use server custom SVAR content.

`useSvar:false` means the aliases ignore server custom SVAR content.

`priority:"svar"` means if a server item has the same name as a default item, the server version wins.

`priority:"gvar"` means if a server item has the same name as a default item, the default version wins.

`unlockMode:"unlocked"` means visible content is usable by default unless specifically locked.

`unlockMode:"locked"` means content must be unlocked before it is visible or usable.

`unlockCvar:"activity_unlocks"` is the character cvar used for player-specific unlocks.

## Recommended Normal Setup

Most servers should use:

```text
!svar activitySources {"useGvar":true,"useSvar":true,"priority":"svar","unlockMode":"unlocked","unlockCvar":"activity_unlocks","setupGuideUrl":"https://github.com/Death8673/Activities/blob/main/Setup"}
```

This uses Death's default content and lets server owners add extra content through svars.

## Server-Only Setup

Use this if the server wants to ignore all default GVAR content and only use custom server svars:

```text
!svar activitySources {"useGvar":false,"useSvar":true,"priority":"svar","unlockMode":"unlocked","unlockCvar":"activity_unlocks","setupGuideUrl":"https://github.com/Death8673/Activities/blob/main/Setup"}
```

If no server content exists, the activity aliases should show **No Entries** and should not spend stamina.

## Locked Progression Setup

Use this if players should only see content they have unlocked:

```text
!svar activitySources {"useGvar":true,"useSvar":true,"priority":"svar","unlockMode":"locked","unlockCvar":"activity_unlocks","setupGuideUrl":"https://github.com/Death8673/Activities/blob/main/Setup"}
```

Unlock examples:

```text
!unlock add fish:*
!unlock add mine:*
!unlock add Copper Ore
!unlock add moonsteel_smithing
```

## Stamina Settings

Create this server svar:

```text
!svar staminaSettings {"mode":"daily","max":100,"reset_hour":0,"timezone_offset":-5,"interval_minutes":0,"regen_amount":0}
```

### Daily Mode

```json
{"mode":"daily","max":100,"reset_hour":0,"timezone_offset":-5,"interval_minutes":0,"regen_amount":0}
```

This resets stamina to full once per server day.

### Regen Mode

```json
{"mode":"regen","max":100,"reset_hour":0,"timezone_offset":-5,"interval_minutes":30,"regen_amount":5}
```

This regenerates stamina over time.

## Server Content Svars

Server owners can add content with layered svars.

The system supports base, `_1`, `_2`, and `_3` versions.

Example:

```text
fish_items
fish_items_1
fish_items_2
fish_items_3
```

This lets staff split large data into smaller svars.

## Gathering Item Svars

Use these for gathering aliases:

```text
fish_items
forage_items
mine_items
track_items
bug_items
wood_items
```

Layered versions also work:

```text
fish_items_1
fish_items_2
fish_items_3
mine_items_1
mine_items_2
mine_items_3
```

Example:

```text
!svar mine_items {"items":{"Moonsteel Ore":{"name":"Moonsteel Ore","category":"ore","rarity":"rare","dc":18,"weight":2,"value_cp":2000,"description":"Rare silver-blue ore found under moonlit stone.","image":"https://example.com/moonsteel-ore.png","tags":["ore","metal","moonsteel"]}}}
```

## Material Svars

Use these for materials that can be used in recipes:

```text
activity_materials
activity_materials_1
activity_materials_2
activity_materials_3
```

You can also use activity-specific material svars:

```text
smithing_materials
weaving_materials
alchemy_materials
make_materials
bakery_materials
```

Example:

```text
!svar activity_materials {"items":{"Fine Sand":{"name":"Fine Sand","category":"sand","rarity":"common","value_cp":5,"description":"Fine pale sand useful in glassmaking.","tags":["sand","glassmaking","fine material"]},"Iron Ingot":{"name":"Iron Ingot","category":"metal","rarity":"common","value_cp":100,"description":"A refined bar of iron.","tags":["metal","iron","ingot"]}}}
```

Tags and categories matter. They allow recipes to use requirements like:

```yaml
category: sand
tag: metal
any_tag: herb
```

## Recipe Svars

Use these for production aliases:

```text
smithing_recipes
weaving_recipes
make_recipes
alchemy_recipes
bakery_recipes
```

Layered versions also work:

```text
smithing_recipes_1
smithing_recipes_2
smithing_recipes_3
alchemy_recipes_1
alchemy_recipes_2
alchemy_recipes_3
```

Example smithing recipe:

```text
!svar smithing_recipes {"recipes":{"Moonsteel Dagger":{"name":"Moonsteel Dagger","production":"smithing","category":"weapon","dc":16,"stamina":10,"creates":1,"value_cp":25000,"description":"A pale silver-blue dagger made from moonsteel.","image":"https://example.com/moonsteel-dagger.png","requires":[{"item":"Moonsteel Ingot","qty":1},{"item":"Weapon Handle","qty":1},{"tag":"leather","qty":1}]}}}
```

Example weaving recipe:

```text
!svar weaving_recipes {"recipes":{"Silken Test Rope":{"name":"Silken Test Rope","production":"weaving","category":"adventuring gear","dc":12,"stamina":8,"creates":1,"value_cp":1000,"description":"A server-only rope recipe for testing.","requires":[{"tag":"fibre","qty":2},{"item":"Fine Sand","qty":1}]}}}
```

Example alchemy recipe:

```text
!svar alchemy_recipes {"recipes":{"Server Healing Salve":{"name":"Server Healing Salve","production":"alchemy","category":"potion","dc":12,"stamina":8,"creates":1,"value_cp":500,"description":"A server-only healing salve.","requires":[{"tag":"herb","qty":2},{"category":"water","qty":1}]}}}
```

Example bakery recipe:

```text
!svar bakery_recipes {"recipes":{"Server Test Bread":{"name":"Server Test Bread","production":"bakery","category":"food","dc":9,"stamina":5,"creates":1,"value_cp":20,"description":"A test loaf from server-only content.","requires":[{"tag":"flour","qty":1},{"category":"water","qty":1}]}}}
```

## Lock and Unlock Svars

Server-wide locks can be added with:

```text
activity_locks
activity_locks_1
activity_locks_2
activity_locks_3
```

Example:

```text
!svar activity_locks ["moonsteel_smithing"]
```

Server-wide unlocks can be added with:

```text
activity_unlocks
activity_unlocks_1
activity_unlocks_2
activity_unlocks_3
```

Character-specific unlocks use the character cvar named in `activitySources`, usually:

```text
activity_unlocks
```

Example character cvar value:

```json
["fish:*","mine:*","Copper Ore","moonsteel_smithing"]
```

## Useful Test Commands

After setup, test these:

```text
!stamina
!fish
!mine
!forage
!track
!bug
!wood

!book fish
!book mine
!book smithing
!book weaving
!book alchemy
!book bakery

!book smithing achievements
!book weaving achievements
!book alchemy achievements

!catalogue sand
!catalogue healing potion
!catalogue ready weaving
!catalogue close weaving

!smithing sword
!weaving rope
!alchemy salve
!bakery bread
```

## Important Notes

If `useGvar:false` and `useSvar:true`, only server svar content should appear.

If the server svars are empty, activities should show **No Entries** and should not spend stamina.

If `unlockMode:"locked"`, locked content should not appear or be usable unless unlocked.

Item and recipe pictures use the large `image`.

Character portraits use the embed thumbnail.
